About

Spice Wannabe Show at the Excalibur Hotel, Las Vegas
Jul 2024 • Family
If you're in Las Vegas, catching the Spice Wannabe show at the Excalibur Hotel is an absolute must, whether you're a die-hard Spice Girls fan or not. This high-energy tribute brings back the iconic '90s girl power vibe in an exhilarating and unforgettable performance.

The talent on stage is undeniable. Each of the ladies delivers exceptional vocals and dynamic dance routines, perfectly capturing the essence of the original Spice Girls. Their chemistry is palpable, and their enthusiasm is infectious, drawing the audience into every song and dance number.

The production quality is top-notch. The choreography is tight and well-executed, showcasing the performers' versatility and dedication. The male dancers add an extra layer of excitement to the show, complementing the main acts with their impressive moves and charisma.

The costumes are a highlight, faithfully recreating the Spice Girls' iconic outfits with a fresh and dazzling twist. From Posh's sleek and stylish looks to Sporty's athletic wear, each costume change brings a new level of visual delight.

The showroom itself is fantastic, offering great views from every seat and an intimate atmosphere that makes you feel part of the action. It's the perfect setting for a show that thrives on audience interaction and high energy.

Speaking of favorites, Posh Spice stood out for me. Her performance was particularly captivating, balancing sophistication and flair, and bringing a unique charm to the stage.

Overall, the Spice Wannabe show is a thrilling tribute that delivers on all fronts—music, dance, and nostalgia. It's a well-produced, brilliantly choreographed spectacle that promises a great time for everyone. Don’t miss it!
Review of: Spice Wannabe: The Spice Girls Tribute at The Excalibur Hotel

Is there an indoor pool or are the outdoor pools open at the end of February?
Written January 18, 2019
john f
Kuwait City, Kuwait
50 contributions
If you are asking about the Excalibur specifically, they have an outdoor pool, most all casinos on the strip have one. Most are nice and well taken care of. As far as an indoor pool, I don't know if the Excalibur has one. The weather at the end of February in Las Vegas is still quite cool. But sometimes it can be in the 70's, I say pack your swimming trunks anyway, they don't take up much space and you might get lucky and have higher temperatures. If you are staying at the Excalibur, you are not far away from the Luxor casino, they have an awesome Titanic museum inside there. Well worth going and seeing it. Have a safe trip.
